-=  In Dreams =-

2
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:46,800
(Man shouts )

3
00:03:46,880 --> 00:03:49,200
(Woman ) Mirror, mirror, on the wall,

4
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:52,240
who's the fairest of us all?

5
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:57,200
(Girl) You're the fairest in
this hall, but Snow White is the...

6
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:59,760
(Chuckles ) Come on, Rebecca.
Forget it's a play.

7
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:02,120
Just say it
like you're saying it to me.

8
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:04,080
Snow White's the fairest of them all

9
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:07,760
And again. Mirror, mirror, on the
wall, who's the fairest of us all?.

10
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:10,000
- You're the fairest in...
- Wrong.

11
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:12,080
You are.

12
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:15,600
What are they doing, Mommy?

13
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:19,800
Nothing, Rebecca.
Daddy'll be home soon.

14
00:04:19,840 --> 00:04:21,920
Last to the car's a bag of rats!

15
00:04:21,960 --> 00:04:23,800
(Dog barks )

16
00:04:23,880 --> 00:04:26,880
(Rebecca ) You never knew
I was a bag of rats!

17
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:52,360
(Rebecca ) Daddy!

18
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:54,120
Daddy!

19
00:04:55,960 --> 00:04:58,920
Hey. Hey, sweetie.

20
00:04:58,960 --> 00:05:01,560
- (Rebecca ) The goldfish died.
- Oh, no.

21
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:04,200
- He did?
- He started to swim backwards.

22
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:07,560
Mom froze him so we could
bury him when you come back.

23
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:10,840
- You want something to eat?
- Breakfast and lunch.

24
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:15,280
- Mary's made spaghetti.
- Oh, God. It's 2am for me, honey.

25
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:17,560
I'm sorry. What are these?

26
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:19,440
- Nothing.
- That's Snow White.

27
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:21,640
Show Daddy your costume, honey.

28
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:24,960
No, I don't want to.
I wanna show him the goldfish.

29
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,760
OK.

30
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:30,520
What is this?
Little Red Riding Hood?

31
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:33,560
No. It's nothing
to do with anything.

32
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,720
It's just another weird dream.

33
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:39,320
Oh, no. Not like the one you had
before my mother died, is it?

34
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:41,240
- No.
- Good.

35
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:44,480
Not like that one.
This one, it keeps coming back.

36
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:48,560
There's an orchard
and this little girl.

37
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:52,120
That little girl,
she's being led through it.

38
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:56,480
- The little girl that's missing?
- She's holding someone's hand.

39
00:05:56,520 --> 00:06:00,720
It's a man or a woman...
with red hair.

40
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:04,160
I keep trying to get rid of it.
I can't.

41
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:06,600
I don't know.
What do you want me to say?

42
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:09,320
- If it's real, go to the cops.
- Paul, please.

43
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:12,640
- I don't know about psychic stuff.
- I hate that word.

44
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:14,880
- So do I.
- What's "physic", Daddy?

45
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:19,600
They're searching the reservoir,
but I have a feeling she's not dead.

46
00:06:19,640 --> 00:06:21,760
What's "physic", Daddy?

47
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:25,000
Psychic is when you can
see through things, like...

48
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:28,040
what's in that big box
that Daddy brought home?

49
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:30,000
Right by the front door.

50
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:31,880
- You got it?
- You bet ya.

51
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:34,480
I tramped all over Tokyo for that.

52
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:37,600
(Motor whining)

53
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:39,960
(Paul) Not too low!

54
00:06:42,280 --> 00:06:44,680
And again. (Chuckles )

55
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:56,000
(Whispers ) Good night, sweetheart.

56
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:58,840
Wasn't that meant for her birthday?

57
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:03,080
Yeah, it was. But I can't be here.
I'm only on a stopover.

58
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:05,440
- Have you told her?
- No.

59
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:07,680
They fucked up my schedule again.

60
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:10,400
- What about the play?
- The play's fine.

61
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:13,000
I have to leave for Seattle at eight.

62
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:21,920
Hey. I got you a kimono.

63
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:25,000
(Dog growls)

64
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:35,080
(Dog barks )

65
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:41,400
Hey.

66
00:08:12,840 --> 00:08:15,040
(Girl)
What did you say your name was?

67
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:16,960
(Deep voice ) Red.

68
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:25,320
(Sighs )

69
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:31,440
(Girl) Where are we going?

70
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:37,520
(Gasps )

71
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:40,040
(Sobs )

72
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:42,080
What?

73
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:44,360
What is it?

74
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:49,880
I saw her,
the little girl that's missing.

75
00:08:49,920 --> 00:08:53,280
- I can't help it. I'm sorry.
- Oh, Jesus.

76
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:55,360
I'm sorry.

77
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:03,960
She's so innocent, Paul,
going wherever he asks her.

78
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:07,040
It's somewhere terrible.

79
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:10,400
I told you, if it's real
you should go to the cops.

80
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:16,400
It's worse now. It's like
some storm's about to break.

81
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:20,680
All right, look, honey.
Tomorrow I'll go to the police, OK?

82
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:24,160
I'll tell them whatever it is
you're imagining, all right?

83
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:27,560
I wanna know I'm wrong, Paul,
more than anything.

84
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:29,600
I wanna know it's just a dream.

85
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:32,680
(Paul sighs )

86
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:36,480
Oh, you know, I'm sorry to
keep you waiting, Mr Cooper.

87
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:39,320
- I apologise. Really I do.
- No problem.

88
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:42,640
I hope you understand that,
you know, this is, well...

89
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:45,560
- This has been a very busy week.
- Yeah, yeah.

90
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:47,880
OK, uh, let me...

91
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:50,320
Let me see if I get this right here.

92
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:52,720
Your wife had a headache...

93
00:09:52,760 --> 00:09:55,920
and she saw a vision
of the missing child, right?

94
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:58,160
I wouldn't phrase it like that.

95
00:09:58,200 --> 00:10:01,440
- How would you phrase it?
- She has, um, these dreams.

96
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:03,480
- Is she a clairvoyant?
- No.

97
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:07,320
Does she talk to dead people?
Communicate with the dead?

98
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:09,880
What? Detective, this isn't a seance.

99
00:10:09,920 --> 00:10:12,680
I was gonna ask
does she wear a turban? (Laughs )

100
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:15,360
One of those crystal balls
with a lamp shade?

101
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:17,320
- None of that.
- Just checking.

102
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:19,240
Tell me what happened.

103
00:10:19,280 --> 00:10:22,280
She dreamt the child
was taken to an orchard

104
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:25,560
where terrible things were
happenin' to her. North of here.

105
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:27,480
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

106
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:30,880
In this vision,
did she get a fix on anyone else?

107
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:33,600
Only his hand.
He was holding her hand.

108
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:35,440
The little girl?.

109
00:10:35,520 --> 00:10:37,880
Yeah, but it could've been a woman's.

110
00:10:37,920 --> 00:10:42,960
Could have been... Oh. All right.
OK. OK, sir. Thanks for comin' in.

111
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:47,600
Detective! I'm waitin' here an hour.
My wife isn't makin' this up.

112
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:51,480
I'm not saying she is. It's been
a long day, give me a break.

113
00:10:51,520 --> 00:10:55,400
Based on your information,
I'm lookin' for a man, a woman...

114
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:57,280
It's not really helpin' me.

115
00:10:57,320 --> 00:11:00,120
Listen, listen.
I know you got a tough job.

116
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:02,200
I got a tough job too. I fly 747 s.

117
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:04,560
I got 350 people relyin' on me.

118
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:08,800
So do me a favour. Hear me out.
Don't treat me like I'm a wacko.

119
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:11,280
They already found her, Mr Cooper.

120
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:14,560
Bottom of a storm drain.
Stones in her pockets.

121
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:18,800
So you go back to flyin' your 747 s.
You take care of your people.

122
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:23,440
I gotta get back to the tedious
business of finding who killed her.

123
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:25,600
Thanks for comin' in.

124
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:32,720
There are 12 fairies, Mommy.

125
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:35,440
Oh. But you'll look the best.

126
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:37,920
I'm the only one that talks.

127
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:40,280
OK. Why don't you try it
one more time?

128
00:11:40,360 --> 00:11:43,120
Then we'll go to dance class, OK?
Big breath.

129
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:45,680
Who's the fairest of us all?.

130
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:48,080
You're the fairest in this hall,

131
00:11:48,160 --> 00:11:51,920
but Snow White's
the fairest...of them all.

132
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:53,400
Very good.

133
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:56,960
(Paul) Claire?

134
00:11:58,720 --> 00:12:00,120
Hon?

135
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:09,680
There you are.

136
00:12:09,760 --> 00:12:13,440
You don't have to tell me.
I heard it on the news.

137
00:12:13,480 --> 00:12:15,880
Guess I'm crazy again, huh?

138
00:12:16,760 --> 00:12:19,760
Well, you got it wrong this time.

139
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:22,760
Yeah, I got a lot of things wrong.

140
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:26,520
- What's that mean?
- You know what it means.

141
00:12:26,560 --> 00:12:28,640
I don't. What are you talking about?

142
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:32,840
I'm talking about the girl
you're seeing in Sydney, Australia.

143
00:12:32,880 --> 00:12:36,680
I'm talking about me pretending
it hasn't been happening.

144
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:38,320
Don't look so surprised.

145
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:41,560
I'm not reading your mind
or your fucking letters,

146
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:44,280
but be more discreet
where you put them!

147
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:46,560
I took this girl to dinner once.

148
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:49,960
She got a crush on me.
I fucked up. I'm sorry.

149
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:52,400
Nothing happened.
Honey, listen to me.

150
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:55,520
Nothing happened.
I promise you. I fucked up.

151
00:12:55,560 --> 00:12:58,720
This is what's been
fucking up the schedule?

152
00:12:58,760 --> 00:13:02,400
No, this is not.
My schedule changes without notice.

153
00:13:02,440 --> 00:13:06,480
This isn't about your schedule.
This is about you fucking someone!

154
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:09,120
But I didn't!
I wanted to, but I didn't!

155
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:13,720
Maybe I wouldn't have wanted to

156
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:16,680
if the woman I love
was here once in a while!

157
00:13:16,720 --> 00:13:19,120
I mean, where are you, Claire?

158
00:13:19,160 --> 00:13:22,840
If it's not one obsession,
it's another. You're gone!

159
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:24,840
Daddy, if I was real...

160
00:13:24,880 --> 00:13:27,160
- Hmm?
- ..dishing out wishes...

161
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:29,640
- All right.
- What would you wish?

162
00:13:29,680 --> 00:13:32,160
That I didn't need one.

163
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:35,280
OK, let's go.

164
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:38,240
- My wand cured the rain.
- Oh, thank God for that.

165
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:41,120
Let's take these off,
they'll get bent in the car.

166
00:13:41,160 --> 00:13:44,000
- Are you coming?
- I'm coming in the other car.

167
00:13:44,040 --> 00:13:45,680
- Let's go.
- Why?

168
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:47,920
I have to fly tonight, darlin'.

169
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:50,560
When I come back,
I'll stay much longer.

170
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:52,600
If your mother lets me.

171
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:56,360
Hello, flowers.

172
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:58,280
Hello, birds.

173
00:13:58,320 --> 00:14:00,240
- Hello, Snow White!
- (Screams )

174
00:14:00,280 --> 00:14:03,920
Please don't kill me.
I'm begging you. Please.

175
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:06,680
What have I done?
Please don't kill me.

176
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:09,680
(Fairies ) Please show mercy!

177
00:14:09,960 --> 00:14:12,720
Please show mercy!

178
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:14,560
Please show mercy!

179
00:14:14,720 --> 00:14:17,680
- Please show mercy!
- Run!

180
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:21,600
Run away and never come back
or your stepmother will get you!

181
00:14:21,640 --> 00:14:23,640
(Applause )

182
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:26,960
I'll always remember
her beautiful smile.

183
00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:30,040
She was so very kind.

184
00:14:30,120 --> 00:14:33,040
- She made our house a home.
- She was very nice to us.

185
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:35,120
She so loved animals. (Crying)

186
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:37,040
She cleaned my glasses.

187
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:39,080
- Honey!
- Who is this lovely maiden?

188
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:40,960
- Oops!
- She's Snow White!

189
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,960
What happened to her?

190
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:46,240
(Dwarves )
She got poisoned by the witch.

191
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:48,720
She's the loveliest maiden
I've ever seen.

192
00:14:48,760 --> 00:14:51,120
May I take her home
to my castle so...

193
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:53,680
(All) Will we never see her again?

194
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:56,360
You may come and live
in my castle as well.

195
00:14:56,400 --> 00:14:58,400
(Applause )

196
00:14:58,920 --> 00:15:00,880
Mirror, mirror,

197
00:15:00,960 --> 00:15:03,360
on the wall,

198
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:07,800
who's the fairest one of all?.

199
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:11,600
You are the fairest in this hall,

200
00:15:11,640 --> 00:15:13,720
but Snow White is the fairest...

201
00:15:13,760 --> 00:15:17,400
- of them all.
- (Giggles )

202
00:15:17,440 --> 00:15:19,640
No, no, no!

203
00:15:19,680 --> 00:15:23,160
Snow White's
the fairest of them all!

204
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:25,720
(Screams )

205
00:15:25,760 --> 00:15:28,080
(Giggling and shouting)

206
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:32,320
Hello. There you are.

207
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:36,320
You were so good. You were so good.
OK, hang on a second.

208
00:15:36,400 --> 00:15:39,480
I'll see you in a couple of days, OK?
Bye-bye.

209
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:42,560
Bye. All right, already. I gotta go.

210
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:46,920
Claire, I was stupid, all right?

211
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:49,600
I admit that.
Nothing more. I promise.

212
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:53,440
- OK. Promise?
- It was my fault.

213
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:55,480
- Bye. Bye.
- See you.

214
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:58,960
- I love you.
- I gotta go. All right.

215
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,600
I love you.

216
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:11,440
(Girls shouting)

217
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:13,040
Rebecca?

218
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:17,520
Sweetie? Sorry,
I thought you were my little girl.

219
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:19,440
Honey?

220
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:22,280
Rebecca?

221
00:16:22,320 --> 00:16:24,800
(Shouting)

222
00:16:24,880 --> 00:16:27,280
Rebecca? Rebecca?

223
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:30,600
- Rebecca?
- (Squealing)

224
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:36,360
Rebecca!

225
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:40,280
Rebecca? Rebecca?

226
00:16:45,080 --> 00:16:46,720
Rebecca!

227
00:16:47,680 --> 00:16:49,080
Rebecca!

228
00:16:49,280 --> 00:16:51,480
Rebecca!

229
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:54,960
(Girl) Where are we going?

230
00:16:55,960 --> 00:16:58,160
(Deep voice ) To my house.

231
00:16:58,920 --> 00:17:01,360
(Claire ) Rebecca!

232
00:17:01,400 --> 00:17:05,800
- (Man ) Guys, fan out to the right!
- Rebecca!

233
00:17:05,880 --> 00:17:07,880
- Where are you?
- We'll find her.

234
00:17:07,920 --> 00:17:10,160
Rebecca!

235
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:13,800
Why didn't I know?
Why didn't I see it? Rebecca!

236
00:17:13,840 --> 00:17:18,320
Rebecca! Rebecca!

237
00:17:18,360 --> 00:17:20,960
(Man ) I said, fan out to the right!

238
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:24,120
We're gonna cover
every inch of ground tonight!

239
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:27,560
(Claire ) Rebecca! Rebecca!

240
00:17:27,640 --> 00:17:29,480
Rebecca!

241
00:17:31,960 --> 00:17:34,360
(Wails)

242
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:43,680
Why didn't you tell me? It wasn't
the past, it was the future!

243
00:17:43,720 --> 00:17:45,400
Take it easy, ma'am.

244
00:17:45,440 --> 00:17:47,960
She's gone! You know that!

245
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:51,000
- We don't know that.
- Well, I know it!

246
00:17:56,920 --> 00:18:00,440
(Screaming) Lord!

247
00:18:00,480 --> 00:18:02,520
Lord, let me help her!

248
00:18:02,640 --> 00:18:05,600
Let me help her!

249
00:18:05,680 --> 00:18:08,960
(Groans )

250
00:18:09,120 --> 00:18:12,720
