508
00:40:48,960 --> 00:40:50,520
(Laughs )

509
00:40:50,560 --> 00:40:53,520
- It's from someone else's childhood.
- Whose?

510
00:40:56,640 --> 00:40:58,600
It's, uh...

511
00:41:01,240 --> 00:41:06,160
It's written on the walls
of a boy's room, and, uh,

512
00:41:06,200 --> 00:41:11,200
the boy is chained to the bed,
and the room's filling up with water.

513
00:41:15,640 --> 00:41:19,680
- So it's from a dream?
- Yeah.

514
00:41:19,720 --> 00:41:22,840
And is it connected to
your dream of apples?

515
00:41:22,880 --> 00:41:25,200
Yes. It's the same boy.

516
00:41:26,240 --> 00:41:28,760
But in the orchard dream
it was a man.

517
00:41:28,800 --> 00:41:32,160
- Can't you make sense of it?
- Would you like me to?

518
00:41:32,200 --> 00:41:36,040
Oh, I would love you to!
I-I-I can't make sense of it.

519
00:41:36,120 --> 00:41:37,960
But, um...

520
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:40,400
I have a feeling that...

521
00:41:40,440 --> 00:41:43,200
they're all coming
from the same place.

522
00:41:43,240 --> 00:41:44,880
From you?

523
00:41:44,920 --> 00:41:48,360
- No, no! From him.
- And who is he?

524
00:41:48,400 --> 00:41:50,360
I don't know.

525
00:41:50,400 --> 00:41:52,400
But I think he deserves a name.

526
00:41:54,600 --> 00:41:57,200
We'll call him Red.

527
00:41:57,280 --> 00:41:59,120
It's appropriate.

528
00:42:02,560 --> 00:42:04,400
OK, Claire.

529
00:42:04,480 --> 00:42:06,640
Let's leave it there for the moment.

530
00:42:06,680 --> 00:42:09,160
OK. (Sighs )

531
00:42:12,440 --> 00:42:16,800
We're gonna take you to get an ECG
and check your blood pressure.

532
00:42:16,840 --> 00:42:21,040
- Are you gonna keep me here?
- We'll supplement your medication.

533
00:42:21,080 --> 00:42:23,080
Mr Cooper, please come in.

534
00:42:24,200 --> 00:42:26,080
Oh.

535
00:42:27,680 --> 00:42:29,520
Take a seat.

536
00:42:31,080 --> 00:42:33,320
(Mary ) Where are you, boy?

537
00:42:33,360 --> 00:42:35,360
Here, boy!

538
00:42:38,120 --> 00:42:40,440
Dobie!

539
00:42:40,480 --> 00:42:42,720
- Dobie!
- What?

540
00:42:42,760 --> 00:42:45,400
He's been missing all day.

541
00:42:45,440 --> 00:42:47,320
Oh, great.

542
00:42:47,360 --> 00:42:49,360
How is she?

543
00:42:49,760 --> 00:42:52,520
They want me
to sign her into Stapleton.

544
00:42:52,560 --> 00:42:56,120
I'm sorry.
I feel like it's all my fault.

545
00:42:57,720 --> 00:43:00,120
It's not your fault, Mary.

546
00:43:03,080 --> 00:43:04,920
Dobie!

547
00:43:05,200 --> 00:43:07,040
Dobie!

548
00:43:08,720 --> 00:43:12,480
- (Growling)
- (Man ) Come on. Come on.

549
00:43:12,520 --> 00:43:15,240
Good boy. Good boy.

550
00:43:15,320 --> 00:43:18,600
- (Whimpering)
- Good boy.

551
00:43:34,960 --> 00:43:37,320
(Barking and whimpering)

552
00:43:52,400 --> 00:43:54,480
Dobie?

553
00:43:57,880 --> 00:44:00,280
Dobie, what is it, boy?

554
00:44:00,840 --> 00:44:03,840
- Dobie? What, boy?
- (Barks )

555
00:44:07,800 --> 00:44:09,640
Dobie!

556
00:44:12,440 --> 00:44:16,600
Dobie? Dobie?

557
00:44:17,640 --> 00:44:19,680
Dobie? Dobie?

558
00:44:19,760 --> 00:44:22,400
(Whimpering and barking)

559
00:44:22,440 --> 00:44:25,160
Dobie! Dobie!

560
00:44:28,320 --> 00:44:30,320
(Horn )

561
00:44:33,400 --> 00:44:36,080
- (Horns honking)
- Dobie!

562
00:44:38,360 --> 00:44:40,200
Dobie!

563
00:45:24,360 --> 00:45:26,720
So what's it gonna be, Paul?.

564
00:45:32,240 --> 00:45:34,080
Stapleton?

565
00:46:02,680 --> 00:46:04,520
(Children laugh)

566
00:46:44,800 --> 00:46:46,840
(Growling)

567
00:46:56,080 --> 00:46:57,880
(Growling continues )

568
00:47:24,840 --> 00:47:26,920
She just woke up.

569
00:47:37,160 --> 00:47:39,960
Stand away from the door, please.

570
00:47:40,560 --> 00:47:43,520
I don't know who you are
or where I am,

571
00:47:43,560 --> 00:47:46,160
but I'm being held against my will,

572
00:47:46,200 --> 00:47:48,280
and I want to use the telephone.

573
00:47:48,320 --> 00:47:50,280
I'd like you to sit on the bed.

574
00:47:50,320 --> 00:47:54,200
I've found my husband's dead body,
and I want the phone!

575
00:47:54,240 --> 00:47:56,760
After you've seen Dr Silverman.

576
00:47:56,840 --> 00:47:59,840
- What is this place?
- Stapleton Hospital.

577
00:47:59,880 --> 00:48:02,200
This is Rosco, and I'm Nurse Floyd.

578
00:48:02,240 --> 00:48:05,720
Well, fuck both of you.
I want Silverman in here now!

579
00:48:05,760 --> 00:48:08,760
- And I want a phone!
- You're not listening.

580
00:48:08,840 --> 00:48:11,160
I just explained about the phone.

581
00:48:11,200 --> 00:48:13,080
Why don't you understand?

582
00:48:13,120 --> 00:48:15,680
I was just in the Carlton Hotel,

583
00:48:15,760 --> 00:48:19,120
and in room 401 is the body
of my murdered husband.

584
00:48:19,160 --> 00:48:21,120
Want me to put her on the bed?

585
00:48:21,160 --> 00:48:24,280
- I'm just gonna put you...
- No! I'll kill you!

586
00:48:24,320 --> 00:48:28,200
- Can I call someone for you?
- Call the fucking police.

587
00:48:28,240 --> 00:48:32,560
My husband's being eaten by a dog
in a hotel room in Hammond.

588
00:48:35,400 --> 00:48:37,560
(Laughing)

589
00:48:37,600 --> 00:48:39,720
Why are you laughing, Claire?

590
00:48:42,360 --> 00:48:44,440
Cos...

591
00:48:44,520 --> 00:48:46,680
the bastard's in my head.

592
00:48:47,680 --> 00:48:49,880
He's fucked up my brain.

593
00:48:50,160 --> 00:48:52,520
And now he's murdered my husband.

594
00:48:54,760 --> 00:48:56,440
Oh.

595
00:48:56,640 --> 00:48:59,400
Oh, God!

596
00:48:59,440 --> 00:49:02,840
- It's happening again!
- What's happening, Claire?

597
00:49:02,880 --> 00:49:06,040
What? What are they doing?

598
00:49:06,240 --> 00:49:10,120
NO! NO!

599
00:49:10,160 --> 00:49:12,040
(Claire screams )

600
00:49:15,320 --> 00:49:17,360
(Rosco ) We're here to help.

601
00:49:22,240 --> 00:49:24,240
How is she?

602
00:49:24,800 --> 00:49:26,800
Terrible.

603
00:49:26,840 --> 00:49:29,240
I'm gonna sell this house.

604
00:49:30,920 --> 00:49:34,200
I need to get her a new shrink.

605
00:49:34,240 --> 00:49:36,320
Want a second opinion?

606
00:49:36,360 --> 00:49:38,720
Yeah. I want 20 of 'em.

607
00:49:38,760 --> 00:49:42,400
Whatever it takes
to get her out of that place.

608
00:49:42,440 --> 00:49:44,040
(Phone )

609
00:49:49,480 --> 00:49:53,720
There's a lady on the phone.
Says she found Dobie near some hotel.

610
00:49:54,480 --> 00:49:56,480
- Hello?
- 'Mr Cooper?'

611
00:50:05,160 --> 00:50:09,360
(Groggily) Doctor, don't...don't
let Paul go to the hotel.

612
00:50:09,400 --> 00:50:11,400
Don't let him go.

613
00:50:12,320 --> 00:50:16,160
- Is this a real hotel?.
- It doesn't matter. The Carlton.

614
00:50:16,200 --> 00:50:18,880
It's by the ocean in Hammond.

615
00:50:18,920 --> 00:50:22,960
- When were you there?
- Last night, room 401.

616
00:50:23,000 --> 00:50:26,360
So it's not real. You dreamt it.

617
00:50:26,400 --> 00:50:29,800
- Was it day or night?
- Daytime. Please call him.

618
00:50:41,320 --> 00:50:44,120
(Silverman )
Does he meet someone there?

619
00:50:44,160 --> 00:50:48,520
- He goes to find Dobie.
- Is Dobie a woman, Claire?

620
00:50:48,600 --> 00:50:50,440
(Groaning)

621
00:50:53,360 --> 00:50:55,360
He's a fucking dog.

622
00:51:09,000 --> 00:51:13,240
What have you given me, Doctor?
Why can't I think straight?

623
00:51:13,280 --> 00:51:17,120
Thorazine. It calms you down.

624
00:51:21,160 --> 00:51:24,160
(Silverman )
'What happens to him there?'

625
00:51:24,720 --> 00:51:26,720
(Claire ) 'He dies.'

626
00:51:26,760 --> 00:51:29,280
(Sobbing) Doctor...

627
00:51:30,320 --> 00:51:34,840
Don't you get it, Doctor?
401. Room 401.

628
00:51:34,920 --> 00:51:37,120
How many times do I have to say it?

629
00:51:37,160 --> 00:51:40,640
(Silverman )
'So you dreamt that Paul died.'

630
00:51:40,680 --> 00:51:44,120
I dreamt it and it happens.

631
00:51:45,560 --> 00:51:47,560
It's going to happen.

632
00:51:47,600 --> 00:51:51,640
Can't you get it through
your thick psytiactric skull?.

633
00:51:51,680 --> 00:51:55,640
The man I love is dead and I'm left
in this God-awful place alone!

634
00:51:57,960 --> 00:51:59,360
Hello?

635
00:51:59,400 --> 00:52:01,920
(Silverman )
'You mean dead to you, Claire.'

636
00:52:01,960 --> 00:52:04,840
No, no, I mean dead like Rebecca.

637
00:52:04,880 --> 00:52:07,520
How many ways can I fucking say it?

638
00:52:08,320 --> 00:52:10,160
Do...

639
00:52:12,000 --> 00:52:15,680
- What the fuck?
- (Silverman ) 'It's called grief.'

640
00:52:15,720 --> 00:52:18,480
No, no, it's Paul this time.

641
00:52:19,480 --> 00:52:21,960
Please. God, listen to me.

642
00:52:22,000 --> 00:52:24,480
- (Whimpering)
- What's this?

643
00:52:25,480 --> 00:52:26,720
Listen to me!

644
00:52:27,440 --> 00:52:29,440
Hi, Paul!

645
00:52:29,880 --> 00:52:31,120
Shit!

646
00:52:31,160 --> 00:52:32,960
(Alarm )

647
00:52:36,640 --> 00:52:39,600
Listen to me! Listen to me!

648
00:52:39,640 --> 00:52:43,560
- Listen to me! Oh! No!
- Come on. Get up.

649
00:52:43,640 --> 00:52:45,840
Come on!

650
00:52:46,120 --> 00:52:48,480
(Claire ) Listen!

651
00:52:48,520 --> 00:52:52,280
Listen to me!

652
00:52:52,320 --> 00:52:54,120
Listen!

653
00:52:54,160 --> 00:52:58,320
(Rosco ) OK, we're going
to give you something to relax.

654
00:52:58,360 --> 00:53:00,920
All right, get her down.

655
00:53:00,960 --> 00:53:04,920
- Please, let me go!
- Just relax.

656
00:53:04,960 --> 00:53:08,640
- Please, no.
- We're going to give you something.

657
00:53:17,720 --> 00:53:20,120
Brought you some hot tea, honey.

658
00:53:20,160 --> 00:53:22,400
It'll still be warm.

659
00:53:22,440 --> 00:53:26,920
- I'm sorry. Do I know you?
- You're sharin' a room with me.

660
00:53:26,960 --> 00:53:30,760
- They want me to keep an eye on you.
- I don't remember.

661
00:53:30,840 --> 00:53:34,160
- You got some people in your head.
- Hmm.

662
00:54:11,640 --> 00:54:13,640
(Bang)

663
00:54:27,840 --> 00:54:31,840
What's the matter, honey?
You don't like the pattern?

664
00:54:39,080 --> 00:54:41,440
(Whispers ) Can you keep a secret?

665
00:54:41,480 --> 00:54:43,600
(Whispers ) Probably.

666
00:54:45,800 --> 00:54:47,840
You won't think I'm crazy?

667
00:54:47,920 --> 00:54:50,200
(Chuckling) Probably! I mean...

668
00:54:50,240 --> 00:54:54,880
That man in my head was in
this hospital when he was a boy.

669
00:54:54,920 --> 00:54:56,520
How do you know?

670
00:54:56,560 --> 00:55:01,040
He stayed in this room.
He wrote that.

671
00:55:01,120 --> 00:55:03,240
His name's Vivian Thompson.

672
00:55:03,280 --> 00:55:05,280
Ooh, la-la! (Chuckles )

673
00:55:09,840 --> 00:55:12,200
Did anyone ever get out of here?

674
00:55:12,240 --> 00:55:14,840
I wouldn't start thinkin' that.

675
00:55:14,880 --> 00:55:19,440
I'm not talking about me.
I'm talking about somebody else.

676
00:55:19,480 --> 00:55:21,320
It's not that difficult.

677
00:55:21,360 --> 00:55:24,360
When you've been here
as long as I have

678
00:55:24,400 --> 00:55:27,160
you get to know the language
of the place.

679
00:55:27,800 --> 00:55:29,800
Go to sleep.

680
00:55:46,880 --> 00:55:50,360
(Girl) Hi! What's your name?
(Woman ) Ruby!

681
00:55:50,400 --> 00:55:52,400
Oh, sorry. I gotta go.

682
00:55:52,960 --> 00:55:54,840
Ruby!

683
00:55:56,280 --> 00:55:58,200
Come on. I'm runnin' late.

684
00:55:58,280 --> 00:56:01,080
- Mommy's in a hurry.
- You're not my mommy.

685
00:56:01,120 --> 00:56:05,200
(Claire ) 'He's hunting...
looking for another little girl.'

686
00:56:05,280 --> 00:56:10,120
Guess what her name is, Doctor.
Ruby.

687
00:56:10,160 --> 00:56:12,240
And what colour is Ruby, Claire?

688
00:56:12,320 --> 00:56:15,320
Ruby's not a colour, Doctor.
Ruby's a girl.

689
00:56:15,360 --> 00:56:20,040
Red. Why are you obsessed
with that colour, Claire?

690
00:56:20,120 --> 00:56:23,360
I'm not obsessed,
I'm possessed, Doctor.

691
00:56:23,400 --> 00:56:26,200
He's feeding me dreams bit by bit.

692
00:56:27,200 --> 00:56:29,040
Why's that, Claire?

693
00:56:29,120 --> 00:56:33,800
Maybe he's lonely.
Maybe he's lonely, Doctor.

694
00:56:35,240 --> 00:56:37,400
Have you a name for him yet?

695
00:56:37,480 --> 00:56:41,320
Yes, I have.
His name is Vivian. Vivian Thompson.

696
00:56:41,400 --> 00:56:45,240
There's a town covered in water.
Someone left him in it.

697
00:56:45,280 --> 00:56:47,320
He was taken to this hospital.

698
00:56:47,360 --> 00:56:51,200
He stayed in my room
and he's feeding me dreams.

699
00:56:51,240 --> 00:56:53,920
Why do you think that is, Doctor?

700
00:56:54,120 --> 00:56:58,960
Because he wants to stop.
He wants me to stop him.

701
00:56:59,040 --> 00:57:01,400
It sounds psychotic to you,
doesn't it?

702
00:57:01,480 --> 00:57:03,720
You used that word, Claire.

703
00:57:03,800 --> 00:57:07,400
But follow it through,
Doctor, psychotic or not.

704
00:57:07,440 --> 00:57:10,720
I've gotta let him possess me...
surrender...

705
00:57:10,800 --> 00:57:13,280
Let him take me to him.

706
00:57:13,320 --> 00:57:18,400
So what does that make me? Psychotic?
Delusional?. Obsessional?. All three?

707
00:57:18,480 --> 00:57:22,880
If you admit that it's delusional,
we might be getting someplace.

708
00:57:42,280 --> 00:57:44,920
So, what's it say
on the wall, Ethel?.

709
00:57:44,960 --> 00:57:48,000
It's some kind of nursery rhyme.

710
00:57:48,040 --> 00:57:50,640
So, I'm not insane?

711
00:57:51,680 --> 00:57:54,280
Not many of us are, honey.

712
00:57:55,840 --> 00:57:59,080
- Go to sleep.
- That's a good idea.

713
00:57:59,160 --> 00:58:01,520
Sleep's the only way to reach him.

714
00:58:01,560 --> 00:58:06,200
He's out there hunting another
little girl, and I've gotta stop him.

715
00:58:06,880 --> 00:58:11,320
Whatever happens, though, promise me
one thing - don't wake me up.

716
00:58:58,880 --> 00:59:00,720
(Gasps )

717
00:59:33,480 --> 00:59:35,760
(Screaming)

718
00:59:46,400 --> 00:59:48,640
(Screaming continues )

719
01:00:05,360 --> 01:00:07,160
My apologies, Claire.

720
01:03:07,640 --> 01:03:11,360
(Rosco ) That's it, Jodie.
Let the medication do the job.

721
01:03:11,440 --> 01:03:14,080
You just relax and sleep.

722
01:03:14,800 --> 01:03:16,640
You'll be fine.

723
01:03:37,400 --> 01:03:39,280
Oh! Excuse me.

724
01:03:43,760 --> 01:03:45,600
(Crickets chirping)

725
01:04:07,280 --> 01:04:10,160
Hey. You need a lift?

726
01:04:10,200 --> 01:04:12,000
I'm waitin' for Lucy.

727
01:04:12,040 --> 01:04:16,480
- Everything all right?
- No, I...

728
01:04:16,520 --> 01:04:19,400
locked myself out of my car.

729
01:04:19,480 --> 01:04:22,400
Come back to the office.
You can use the phone.

730
01:04:22,480 --> 01:04:27,160
Uh, I have a spare,
uh, set...at a garage.

731
01:04:28,320 --> 01:04:31,440
If you're going out,
you could drop me.

732
01:04:32,120 --> 01:04:35,320
- Which garage?
- The one down the road.

733
01:04:36,240 --> 01:04:39,040
- Got your ID?
- It's locked in the car.

734
01:04:40,200 --> 01:04:42,200
All right. Hop in.

735
01:04:47,720 --> 01:04:52,720
So, uh, do you want to get a drink
or something like that?

736
01:04:52,760 --> 01:04:55,800
Yeah, maybe. Whatever you wanna do.

737
01:05:07,600 --> 01:05:10,040
(Siren wailing)

738
01:05:10,080 --> 01:05:14,920
- Could we have some music?
- Music? Sure.

739
01:05:18,240 --> 01:05:20,680
( Quiet music)

740
01:05:21,360 --> 01:05:23,160
You work nights.

741
01:05:23,200 --> 01:05:26,000
- Uh, yeah.
- What's your name?

742
01:05:26,040 --> 01:05:30,320
- Vivienne. What's yours?
- Walter.

743
01:05:32,400 --> 01:05:36,360
That's a nice name, Vivienne.
Hey, how you spell that?

744
01:05:36,400 --> 01:05:39,200
V-I-V-I-E-N-N-E.

745
01:05:43,360 --> 01:05:46,160
Can't keep your eyes off me,
can you?

746
01:05:46,200 --> 01:05:49,200
- Off what, Vivienne?
- My legs.

747
01:05:51,080 --> 01:05:53,600
Pity to leave you so soon,
Vivienne.

748
01:05:53,640 --> 01:05:57,600
Well...I'm in no real hurry.

749
01:05:58,640 --> 01:06:02,320
Well, what do you know? Neither am I.

750
01:06:05,520 --> 01:06:09,280
You've been eating those knees
the whole way.

751
01:06:09,320 --> 01:06:11,840
Shouldn't your eyes have been
on the road?

752
01:06:11,880 --> 01:06:13,720
I suppose they should've.

753
01:06:16,000 --> 01:06:18,040
You can kiss me if you want.

754
01:06:19,040 --> 01:06:21,360
Don't mind if I do.

755
01:06:23,960 --> 01:06:25,360
(Giggling)

756
01:06:26,920 --> 01:06:29,040
- What the fuck?
- (Laughs )

757
01:06:30,160 --> 01:06:32,280
Two things, Walter.

758
01:06:32,360 --> 01:06:36,160
- One, get out of the car slowly.
- Mm-hmm.

759
01:06:36,200 --> 01:06:40,840
And two, get your ass back
to Stapleton and tell Silverman

760
01:06:40,880 --> 01:06:43,280
to check out the Carlton Hotel.

761
01:06:56,960 --> 01:06:59,080
Why are we here?

762
01:06:59,120 --> 01:07:01,360
That's my home.

763
01:07:01,400 --> 01:07:04,040
A lake? You live in a lake?

764
01:07:06,240 --> 01:07:08,280
Did once.

765
01:07:16,480 --> 01:07:18,320
(Splash)

766
01:07:39,800 --> 01:07:42,600
(Whispering)
Where did you go, Vivian?

767
01:07:44,160 --> 01:07:46,680
Please, please don't leave me now.

768
01:07:49,760 --> 01:07:52,760
(Footsteps )

769
01:08:10,240 --> 01:08:13,040
Wanna come over to my house, Claire?

770
01:08:13,720 --> 01:08:15,560
Yeah.

771
01:08:15,640 --> 01:08:18,800
I have to warn you, it's haunted.

772
01:08:18,880 --> 01:08:21,200
Who's it haunted by?

773
01:08:21,240 --> 01:08:23,120
You.

774
01:08:42,400 --> 01:08:45,600
I'll show you how to get there.
You can drive now.

775
01:08:53,280 --> 01:08:57,920
Vivian, is there a girl
in your house called Ruby?

776
01:08:57,960 --> 01:09:00,280
Ruby? Yeah.

777
01:09:02,760 --> 01:09:06,800
- She's dying to meet you.
- Oh, God.

778
01:09:06,840 --> 01:09:09,080
You thought it was a real orchard?

779
01:09:09,120 --> 01:09:13,280
That's the thing about dreams,
They're always right...

780
01:09:13,320 --> 01:09:15,320
and always wrong.

781
01:09:21,080 --> 01:09:24,360
You have to drive inside, OK?
I'll open the door.

782
01:09:51,200 --> 01:09:53,680
You know this place,
don't you, Claire?

783
01:09:59,040 --> 01:10:02,040
- Yes.
- You know the funny thing?

784
01:10:02,080 --> 01:10:04,760
What's the funny thing?

785
01:10:04,800 --> 01:10:10,040
I know you got a gun in the band
of the nurse's dress you're wearing.

786
01:10:10,120 --> 01:10:12,280
- I do?
- You do!

787
01:10:12,320 --> 01:10:16,080
And it's not very nice,
you meetin' Ruby with a gun.

788
01:10:16,120 --> 01:10:19,560
Might get her upset.
Might get me upset...

789
01:10:19,600 --> 01:10:22,360
and bring the apples
down on all of us.

790
01:10:23,520 --> 01:10:26,760
- Where is Ruby?
- Ubi est Ruby?

791
01:10:28,120 --> 01:10:30,840
I'm not tellin'
till you gimme the gun.

792
01:10:41,200 --> 01:10:44,200
You know what happens
when the apples fall?.

793
01:10:44,240 --> 01:10:45,800
I don't.

794
01:10:52,600 --> 01:10:57,480
# First the tide

795
01:10:58,520 --> 01:11:00,600
# Rushes in

796
01:11:02,600 --> 01:11:06,760
# Plants a kiss

797
01:11:06,840 --> 01:11:09,880
# On the shore

798
01:11:10,760 --> 01:11:14,560
# Then rolls... #

799
01:11:14,600 --> 01:11:19,080
I'm so, so
sorry, sorry, sorry, Claire.

800
01:11:20,600 --> 01:11:22,960
All I wanted was a family.

801
01:11:23,000 --> 01:11:28,120
I knew there was a dreamer out there
like me, cos I was dreamin' of her.

802
01:11:28,200 --> 01:11:30,440
I wanted her to be my family.

803
01:11:32,040 --> 01:11:35,080
And I took her little girl.

804
01:11:35,160 --> 01:11:39,400
And the little girl cried
and hollered,

805
01:11:40,680 --> 01:11:44,400
and I punished her
like any dad would.

806
01:11:46,160 --> 01:11:48,160
- And she was lying...
- (Sobbing)

807
01:11:48,240 --> 01:11:51,160
quiet, beautiful...

808
01:11:52,200 --> 01:11:54,240
but like a doll now.

809
01:11:55,960 --> 01:11:58,440
- That's the part I'm sorry for.
- (Gasping)

810
01:11:58,480 --> 01:12:00,800
But I'm gonna make it up to you.

811
01:12:00,880 --> 01:12:02,880
I'm gonna work...

812
01:12:02,920 --> 01:12:04,920
real hard.

813
01:12:05,120 --> 01:12:07,120
Make it perfect.

814
01:12:07,880 --> 01:12:11,720
I'm not gonna get upset anymore
now that I've got you here,

815
01:12:11,760 --> 01:12:14,160
and I got us Ruby for a daughter now.

816
01:12:16,240 --> 01:12:19,600
Claire and Vivian and Ruby.
(Chuckles )

817
01:12:20,760 --> 01:12:24,920
Did you... Did you get upset
with Ruby, Vivian?

818
01:12:24,960 --> 01:12:27,000
- Not yet. Not yet.
- Did you?

819
01:12:27,080 --> 01:12:29,200
Are you gonna get upset with me?

820
01:12:30,720 --> 01:12:34,360
Not if you love me
like Mama loves Dad. Will you?

821
01:12:35,360 --> 01:12:37,720
I'll do that, Vivian.

822
01:12:39,880 --> 01:12:41,880
I'll do that.

823
01:12:42,960 --> 01:12:45,760
You wouldn't just pretend?

824
01:12:45,840 --> 01:12:47,840
How could I pretend?

825
01:12:49,760 --> 01:12:52,760
How could I pretend with you, Vivian?

826
01:12:52,800 --> 01:12:55,640
You know me inside and out.

827
01:12:55,680 --> 01:12:58,040
Things are gonna be perfect...

828
01:12:59,080 --> 01:13:01,080
when I see Ruby.

829
01:13:02,200 --> 01:13:05,480
As perfect as they can be
in this valley of tears.

830
01:13:16,680 --> 01:13:20,480
- Oh, Lordy.
- What the fuck is this?

831
01:13:20,520 --> 01:13:24,240
Her dream, Rosco. Your nightmare.

832
01:13:27,320 --> 01:13:30,920
(Vivian ) Ruby, guess who's here?
Say hi to Ruby, Claire.

833
01:13:36,200 --> 01:13:39,120
- Hello, Ruby.
- Are you a ghost?

834
01:13:39,200 --> 01:13:40,840
No, I'm not.

835
01:13:40,880 --> 01:13:45,840
She was a ghost when she wasn't here.
Now she's just plain old Claire.

836
01:13:45,880 --> 01:13:51,040
Why don't you go down in the garden
and show Ruby you're not a ghost?

837
01:13:51,080 --> 01:13:54,480
He said you were coming.
You took a long time.

838
01:13:55,200 --> 01:13:59,280
I know. It was gettin' kinda lonesome
here just the two of us, huh?

839
01:13:59,320 --> 01:14:02,280
I suppose. This is Marge.

840
01:14:02,320 --> 01:14:05,800
She was Vivian's doll
before he gave her to me.

841
01:14:05,840 --> 01:14:11,240
Say hello to Claire, Marge.
That nice lady is not a ghost.

842
01:14:11,280 --> 01:14:13,440
Hello, Claire! Welcome home!

843
01:14:14,480 --> 01:14:16,720
Welcome home, Claire.

844
01:14:18,080 --> 01:14:20,480
- She's followed him.
- Who?

845
01:14:20,520 --> 01:14:24,800
Vivian Thompson. He escaped
through that grate. Murdered a nurse.

846
01:14:24,840 --> 01:14:27,680
- When?
- 25 years ago. October 1972.

847
01:14:27,720 --> 01:14:30,160
- I'm lost, Doctor.
- Join the club.

848
01:14:31,200 --> 01:14:33,200
He killed her daughter.

849
01:14:34,000 --> 01:14:38,600
She shares his dreams. He snatched
another little girl called Ruby.

850
01:14:42,000 --> 01:14:45,960
She's gone to stop him.
Call the police. Show them this.

851
01:14:46,040 --> 01:14:49,760
- Where are you going?
- Hammond, the Carlton Hotel.

852
01:14:50,560 --> 01:14:53,240
I'll make us somethin' to eat.
Is anyone hungry?

853
01:14:53,320 --> 01:14:55,160
How about "pasghetti"?

854
01:14:58,480 --> 01:15:01,840
Daddies can be just like mommies,
you know that?

855
01:15:01,880 --> 01:15:06,320
- Can they, honey?
- Vivian said so. They can cook too.

856
01:15:10,160 --> 01:15:12,400
What else did he tell you, Ruby?

857
01:15:12,440 --> 01:15:15,920
Told me my real mom
is up in Heaven waiting for me.

858
01:15:17,360 --> 01:15:19,240
That's Vivian's mom there.

859
01:15:19,280 --> 01:15:21,760
(Claire )
That's a tailor's dummy, Ruby.

860
01:15:21,800 --> 01:15:24,920
I know, but that's
the kind of clothes she wore.

861
01:15:24,960 --> 01:15:27,840
- Why does he keep them?
- For playing mom.

862
01:15:27,920 --> 01:15:32,600
He's very good at it. You should
hear the way his voice changes.

863
01:15:32,640 --> 01:15:34,720
Why does he do that?

864
01:15:34,760 --> 01:15:38,440
He says his daddy was a dollar
and his mommy was a song.

865
01:15:38,480 --> 01:15:39,800
A song?

866
01:15:39,840 --> 01:15:43,840
"Don't Sit Under The Apple Tree
With Anyone Else But Me."

867
01:15:43,920 --> 01:15:46,400
So that's his mother's song.

868
01:15:46,440 --> 01:15:48,840
That's what she was, that song.

869
01:16:01,760 --> 01:16:03,760
I don't like the cold.

870
01:16:05,640 --> 01:16:07,720
Ruby...

871
01:16:07,800 --> 01:16:10,000
Ruby, listen to me, OK?

872
01:16:10,040 --> 01:16:13,000
Vivian's sick, honey,
and he needs help.

873
01:16:13,040 --> 01:16:17,240
- It's possible he could hurt you.
- You're scaring me.

874
01:16:17,320 --> 01:16:20,720
- I'm gonna take you away from here.
- Vivian!

875
01:16:20,800 --> 01:16:23,320
Shh! Quiet!

876
01:16:23,360 --> 01:16:27,880
I've been looking for the can opener,
but I can't...find it!

877
01:16:29,920 --> 01:16:31,920
I know it's down there.

878
01:16:33,840 --> 01:16:37,120
Sometimes Mommy and Daddy fight
and that's bad.

879
01:16:37,160 --> 01:16:39,960
Sometimes they fight and that's good.

880
01:16:42,560 --> 01:16:45,040
She's so, so, so tired.

881
01:16:46,280 --> 01:16:48,280
You help me find it?

882
01:16:48,320 --> 01:16:52,920
Cos you're the girl. And when we
find it you can have some...snacks.

883
01:16:52,960 --> 01:16:55,920
And then when she wakes up
we'll feed her too.

884
01:16:57,280 --> 01:16:59,400
You gonna say you're sorry now?

885
01:16:59,440 --> 01:17:02,920
# Don't sit under the apple tree
with anyone else but me

886
01:17:02,960 --> 01:17:04,400
# Anyone else but me... #

887
01:17:04,440 --> 01:17:08,440
Cat got your tongue?
You're worse than your goddam daddy!

888
01:17:08,520 --> 01:17:12,040
# Don't sit under the apple tree
with anyone else but me

889
01:17:12,080 --> 01:17:15,840
# Till I come marching home... #

890
01:17:16,880 --> 01:17:19,280
(Song continues, muffled)

891
01:17:23,200 --> 01:17:25,080
(Whimpers )

892
01:17:30,480 --> 01:17:33,640
(Ruby ) You got him real mad.

893
01:17:34,920 --> 01:17:38,360
That's why he put you
in bad mommy's clothes.

894
01:17:38,400 --> 01:17:40,840
He says he's disappointed in you.

895
01:17:40,880 --> 01:17:45,800
He told me you'd be the loveliest
mommy in the whole wide world.

896
01:17:49,160 --> 01:17:51,160
Does your face hurt?

897
01:17:52,200 --> 01:17:54,240
I can kiss it better.

898
01:17:55,400 --> 01:17:58,360
Is that better?
Are you tied too tight?

899
01:17:58,400 --> 01:18:01,160
I'd loosen it,
but he might get mad again.

900
01:18:01,200 --> 01:18:04,440
- I'd never seen him mad before.
- (Vivian ) Ruby!

901
01:18:19,040 --> 01:18:21,360
- Dr Silverman?
- Yeah.

902
01:18:21,400 --> 01:18:23,640
You know this place?

903
01:18:23,680 --> 01:18:25,720
I was told about it.

904
01:18:25,760 --> 01:18:27,800
Let's get some light in there.

905
01:18:28,160 --> 01:18:30,160
Sweet Jesus!

906
01:18:33,280 --> 01:18:37,480
(Vivian ) # ..with anyone else but me

907
01:18:37,520 --> 01:18:39,920
# Anyone else but me

908
01:18:40,000 --> 01:18:42,000
# With anyone else but me #

909
01:18:43,920 --> 01:18:45,920
Bedtime, Ruby. Undo me, OK?

910
01:18:46,840 --> 01:18:50,640
Time to move over, Claire.
Thank you, sweetums.

911
01:18:50,680 --> 01:18:52,680
Go snuggle up with Mommy.

912
01:18:55,080 --> 01:18:57,720
I'd never hurt you, Claire.

913
01:19:03,560 --> 01:19:07,520
(Chuckles ) Didn't mind
hurting Paul, though, did I?

914
01:19:08,920 --> 01:19:11,280
I thought you'd be a better mommy.

915
01:19:11,320 --> 01:19:13,880
My mom was no good either.

916
01:19:13,920 --> 01:19:15,720
She...

917
01:19:17,040 --> 01:19:19,360
wore dresses like that.

918
01:19:23,800 --> 01:19:26,000
# Never knew my dad

919
01:19:26,080 --> 01:19:28,040
# Mom was all I had #

920
01:19:28,080 --> 01:19:29,520
NO!

921
01:19:33,400 --> 01:19:35,200
Please?

922
01:19:36,480 --> 01:19:38,600
Got eyes in the back of my head.

923
01:19:38,640 --> 01:19:43,560
When Mom said
it was time for bed, I...

924
01:19:43,600 --> 01:19:45,480
I believed her.

925
01:19:45,560 --> 01:19:48,240
Sorry if I'm moody.
It's been a long day.

926
01:19:48,280 --> 01:19:50,560
Things didn't turn out the way...

927
01:19:51,960 --> 01:19:53,960
I thought they would.

928
01:19:57,280 --> 01:20:01,080
Now I'm gonna kiss you...

929
01:20:01,160 --> 01:20:03,720
- good night.
- Ah!

930
01:20:03,800 --> 01:20:06,800
- Ow.
- Take a cheek, Ruby.

931
01:20:39,880 --> 01:20:42,120
(Gasping)

932
01:20:43,280 --> 01:20:45,120
- Oh, God.
- Shh.

933
01:20:45,200 --> 01:20:47,040
- Claire?
- Shh, shh, shh, shh. Yes?

934
01:20:47,120 --> 01:20:48,960
- Claire?
- Yes?

935
01:20:49,040 --> 01:20:51,040
I just had a bad dream.

936
01:20:53,040 --> 01:20:56,040
I dreamt my mommy
was dead in the lake...

937
01:20:57,200 --> 01:20:59,480
and she had your face.

938
01:20:59,520 --> 01:21:01,520
(Sobs )

939
01:21:02,440 --> 01:21:05,240
Does that mean you're gonna kill me?

940
01:21:08,400 --> 01:21:10,400
I hope not.

941
01:21:20,920 --> 01:21:24,880
- Any word on the car she took?
- It was seen on Route Nine.

942
01:21:24,920 --> 01:21:27,120
- Great, let's go.
- All right.

943
01:21:33,520 --> 01:21:35,760
You're not such a bad mom.

944
01:21:39,360 --> 01:21:41,400
Don't get him mad again.

945
01:21:53,160 --> 01:21:54,200
(Screams )

946
01:21:54,240 --> 01:21:56,520
I don't like you any more.

947
01:21:56,560 --> 01:21:59,600
- I die in the lake, remember?
- I forgot that.

948
01:21:59,640 --> 01:22:02,760
- Maybe you develop a limp.
- I emptied it.

949
01:22:04,040 --> 01:22:05,960
(Claire ) Run!

950
01:22:07,400 --> 01:22:09,240
Run, Ruby!

951
01:22:11,160 --> 01:22:14,480
Run! Wait! Stop.

952
01:22:14,520 --> 01:22:17,120
Come here. Now, you gotta
be brave now, Ruby.

953
01:22:17,200 --> 01:22:20,560
- You gotta be brave, honey.
- Yes. You gotta come with me.

954
01:22:20,640 --> 01:22:23,320
- It's me he wants, not you.
- Claire!

955
01:22:26,680 --> 01:22:28,680
Vivian.

956
01:22:31,040 --> 01:22:32,760
Mom?

957
01:22:33,680 --> 01:22:36,480
You gonna say you're sorry now?

958
01:22:37,040 --> 01:22:39,360
I...don't...WANNA!

959
01:22:42,960 --> 01:22:44,960
(Sirens wailing)

960
01:22:46,000 --> 01:22:49,480
Route Nine. Just made visual
contact with ground units.

961
01:22:49,760 --> 01:22:51,840
(Vivian, wailing) Mom!

962
01:22:54,760 --> 01:22:56,760
Something's wrong.

963
01:23:01,960 --> 01:23:03,760
Mom?

964
01:23:05,560 --> 01:23:08,640
(Whispers ) The cat got my tongue.

965
01:23:11,920 --> 01:23:15,880
Mom? It hurts real bad.

966
01:23:15,920 --> 01:23:19,800
Ruby, where the fuck are you?!

967
01:23:26,280 --> 01:23:28,120
(Vivian ) Claire!

968
01:23:40,960 --> 01:23:42,960
It still hurts!

969
01:23:44,320 --> 01:23:46,360
Gonna kiss and make it better!

970
01:23:47,960 --> 01:23:51,480
Every couple has their problems.
We have to talk!

971
01:23:55,600 --> 01:23:57,400
Two-six to dispatch.

972
01:23:57,440 --> 01:24:02,120
I have a young girl fitting
the description of the subject.

973
01:24:02,840 --> 01:24:04,960
Don't you want to work it out?

974
01:24:05,000 --> 01:24:07,640
Or is it just too late
for me and you?

975
01:24:07,680 --> 01:24:11,040
I know how it goes now -
Ruby makes it to the road.

976
01:24:11,080 --> 01:24:13,760
She stops a car, maybe a police car.

977
01:24:13,800 --> 01:24:18,000
The policeman comes in
and there's all this hostage stuff!

978
01:24:18,040 --> 01:24:20,640
- Is that how it goes?
- Uh-huh.

979
01:24:20,680 --> 01:24:23,000
Maybe Claire breaks her neck!

980
01:24:23,040 --> 01:24:26,280
Oh, I don't want this to happen(!)

981
01:24:26,320 --> 01:24:29,320
I really went out of my way
to bring you here!

982
01:24:29,360 --> 01:24:31,640
- Maybe Claire jumps!
- No, please!

983
01:24:35,880 --> 01:24:37,880
Claire!

984
01:24:38,680 --> 01:24:40,560
(Screams ) Claire!

985
01:24:58,000 --> 01:25:02,080
We got a lead. A girl found off
the interstate named Ruby.

986
01:25:02,120 --> 01:25:06,880
Head due east, we're looking
for a large wooden structure.

987
01:25:06,920 --> 01:25:09,480
- A cider factory.
- Roger that.

988
01:25:14,000 --> 01:25:16,120
Claire!

989
01:25:17,360 --> 01:25:19,240
Claire!

990
01:25:20,000 --> 01:25:22,040
Where are you?

991
01:25:38,480 --> 01:25:40,720
(Vivian screams )

992
01:26:20,480 --> 01:26:24,280
This is Air Seven.
Have established visual contact.

993
01:26:25,360 --> 01:26:28,760
Hey! Hey! Hey!

994
01:26:31,880 --> 01:26:33,800
He's back there!

995
01:26:34,040 --> 01:26:35,440
Back there!

996
01:26:38,480 --> 01:26:42,000
Now there's all this hostage stuff.
I told you so!

997
01:26:44,120 --> 01:26:47,560
- You've gotta give yourself up!
- But how?

998
01:26:47,600 --> 01:26:50,680
I let you go,
they'll make a real mess of me.

999
01:26:54,800 --> 01:26:58,800
- It's empty! There's no bullets!
- Go away! Go away!

1000
01:26:59,960 --> 01:27:01,280
Shoot!

1001
01:27:43,440 --> 01:27:45,920
(Rebecca ) Mirror, mirror on the wall

1002
01:27:45,960 --> 01:27:49,200
who's the fairest one of all?.

1003
01:27:49,240 --> 01:27:52,000
You are.

1004
01:27:52,040 --> 01:27:54,840
Wrong. You are.

1005
01:28:18,640 --> 01:28:21,040
Come with me.

1006
01:28:21,560 --> 01:28:23,560
Where, darling?

1007
01:28:25,800 --> 01:28:27,640
Home.

1008
01:28:59,880 --> 01:29:03,080
(Judge ) The jury finds you
guilty, but insane,

1009
01:29:03,120 --> 01:29:05,520
so I cannot pass the death sentence.

1010
01:29:05,560 --> 01:29:08,600
You will be held
in a secure mental facility

1011
01:29:08,680 --> 01:29:12,080
until the state
deems it safe to release you,

1012
01:29:12,120 --> 01:29:14,600
which I hope
will not be in my lifetime.

1013
01:29:16,840 --> 01:29:18,640
